  "text": "In agreement with [CITATION_1] , we found that single doses of morphine and ethanol led to a significant increase (morphine, po0.01; ethanol, po0.001) in the AMPA/ NMDA ratio measured from VTA DA neurons 24 h after the drug injection (Figure 1 ). We also found that a single injection of DZ at a dose of 5 or 20 mg/kg, i.p., significantly (po0.001) increased the AMPA/NMDA ratio in VTA DA neurons (Figure 1) . The effect was similar at both doses, and also very similar to that produced by morphine and ethanol. Behaviorally, the mice showed heavy sedation (loss of locomotor activity) within a few min after the DZ (5 mg/kg, i.p.) injection, and they started to recover around 60 min afterward, with no visible sedation anymore after 2-3 h (based on visual observations of the mouse activity induced by moving the home cage and the lid).",
